      "content": "It is highly unlikely that your smart appliances are detecting your emotions. These devices rely on environmental sensors like temperature and motion, not complex biometric readings from your stress levels. The fluctuations you see are probably coincidental, perhaps triggered by changes in your body heat affecting the local environment or power draw when you move or adjust the devices. My advice is to test this by intentionally changing the room temperature or turning your fridge on/off to see if the behavioral patterns remain consistent.",
