      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While many smart devices have microphones or motion sensors, it is extremely unlikely they are complex enough to interpret human emotional breakdowns. These systems are usually designed for functional tasks like temperature regulation or inventory tracking, not psychological monitoring. If your appliances are recording sound or excessive activity, it is more likely a coincidence amplified by confirmation bias, or a simple temporary software glitch. You might want to check the privacy settings and associated apps for any unexpected data permissions.",
