      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Technically, acoustic sensors can detect specific sound patterns, and motion sensors track activity changes, sending this data via Wi-Fi to cloud servers. The data transmission for these events is usually near real-time, often within a couple of seconds depending on network latency. A sophisticated AI *could* theoretically analyze distress vocalizations, but most consumer devices do not have the advanced, always-on, high-level processing capability for that. It is far more probable that the observed correlation is due to environmental factors or coincidence than intentional emotional monitoring.",
